      "writtenOn": "2018-06-22T21:45:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "we don\u0027t call log inside this loop, so how is this different from just putting all commits into one large slice, sorting by time and returning top limit items?\n\nalso see my another comment. Since we do\u0027t dynamically fetch logs, i think we can just return all commits bundled together. Sorting is not fetching (this is a specific implementation of FetchRefs)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 125,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 142,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "3f84e25dc12859a1c277a5a0125a462ed11c4e67",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
